################################
#        General Syntax        #
################################

# DLScript syntax is relatively simple

# 1. keywords are separated by the 8=D identifier
print 8=D Hello World!
number 8=D num 8=D 9087


# 2. Arguments are separated by the <> identifier
number[] 8=D array 8=D __empty__
append 8=D $array<>129


# 3. The interpreter interpretes the complete line, so each line can only contain 1 function

# this will throw an error if run
print 8=D Hello print 8=D 
World!

# 4. Comments are added by starting a line with the # identifier
# this is a comment